data.enText: not made weaker by having water added to it; not having been diluted
not mixed or combined with anything and therefore very strong
data.chText: 真挚的；纯洁的；浓烈的；醇厚的

example.ex: I will look back at this one with undiluted pleasure...
example.tran: 回顾此事，我会无比地开心。

example.ex: The report had not been received with undiluted enthusiasm...
example.tran: 这份报告并未收到热烈的反响。

example.ex: Her Irish accent, after thirty-odd years in London, is undiluted.
example.tran: 她在伦敦呆了30多年，爱尔兰口音仍很浓重。

value.def: If you describe someone's feelings or characteristics as undiluted, you are emphasizing that they are very strong and not mixed with any other feeling or quality.
A liquid that is undiluted has not been made weak by mixing it with water.
